author: third_watch
title: Hurricane Maria to Hurt Medtronic in Q2, FY18 View Intact
summary: Medtronic (MDT) expects normal manufacturing process in Puerto Rico to resume in full force in the coming weeks with considerable repairing done in the aftermath of Hurricane Maria.

author: captainunderoos
title: FEMA Administrator Rips San Juan Mayor's Criticisms: 'We Don't Have Time for the Political Noise'
summary: FEMA Administrator Brock Long ripped San Juan Mayor Carmen Yulín Cruz for her attacks on the agency Sunday, saying "we filtered out the mayor a long time ago" and he didn't have time for "political noise." President Donald Trump visited the Hurricane Maria devastation in Puerto Rico on Tuesday and praised relief efforts there, but Cruz criticized him for his "abominable" behavior when Trump threw paper towel rolls to storm survivors and said his visit was a publicity stunt. It was the latest in the war of words between the two after Trump said last weekend she had exhibited poor leadership in response to her criticism of the federal response as too slow.
